About
LOOKOUT 360º Amsterdam + sensational swing An iconic viewing point in The Netherlands - A’DAM LOOKOUT, has joined the Eiffel Tower, the Fernsehturm and the London Eye. For the daredevils among us, LOOKOUT also has a further adrenalin kick in store. On the roof is Europe’s highest swing. You swing over the edge of the tower at a thrilling height of almost 100 metres above the ground. Highlights: - The most spectacular view of Amsterdam and the surrounding area - A Bird’s-eye view of Amsterdam from the highest swing in Europe - Access to the indoor interactive state-of-the-art Amsterdam exhibition - Free digital photo of your visit to LOOKOUT - Enjoy coffee, breakfast, lunch, dinner and/or cocktails in Madam Restaurant & Sky Bar - Free WIFI available Payments with cards only.
Duration: 1-2 hours

  • Russ G

    A Swinging Time!
    Just a short ferry ride from Centraal Station, we had a beautiful, sunny day for our trip to the lookout. The experience begins with a Techno-enhanced lift ride to the top, complete with a thrilling light show. Once on top, there are two lookout platforms to help take photos above the screen fence. For the more adventurous, there is "Over The Edge", Europe's highest swing. I will tell you that I am not a fan of roller coasters, or heights, or swinging over the edge of a building, but I wanted to experience it for myself. It is as thrilling and scary as you think it is. I chose to keep my eyes shut for most of it, but feel free to look around (and straight down). It only runs a minute, which was just long enough for me! Afterwards, we enjoyed a drink and soaked in the views. Highly recommended!
    Debby R

    Amazing afternoon with amazing views
    Me and my friend visit whilst on holiday in Amsterdam. We didn’t know about A’DAM LOOKOUT until we got off the train at Amsterdam Centraal. My friend booked the tickets online, which included The Swing, The VR rollercoaster and 2 drinks. Staff we’re all very friendly and helpful. The ride up to the 20th floor in the elevator was unique and fun. The swing was just amazing, such great views. The VR rollercoaster was fun and we enjoyed our drinks (and some Bitterballen) in the bar with some fantastic views across Amsterdam. The audio tour on the Skydeck was very good and gave lots of interesting facts. We will definitely be returning next time we are in Amsterdam.

Observatory deck in Amsterdam, Netherlands
Oct 2024 • Friends
Was it worth $20 USD? Not really. Bought our tickets onsite but I think it’s a bit cheaper if you buy online ahead. But it was still nice to be up so high and see a 360 degree view of the city. The outside observatory deck is skewed with an ugly fence so you can’t take great photos without your view being blocked. The swing is a neat experience if you’re willing to pay extra but the swing isn’t much of a far push outward.

There’s an indoor bar/restaurant below, if you want to grab drinks and get a good 360 degrees view (clear windows). Service at the bar needs improvement, they are not very attentive at all. Cocktails were just okay. Got a side of Parmesan Fries which were good.

Lee T
London, UK90 contributions
Great views although a little pricey
We went here on our last day and the weather wasn’t great but still great views all over Amsterdam and up and down the river. There is an inside 360 viewing area with bar/cafe and plenty of seating and then there is the top deck which is open air. I’m sure on a nice sunny day it is lovely up there in which case you would probably stay longer and make it worth while for the money. If you go then set a side a coupe of hours to make it worth while.

There is also the swing at the top which my wife and daughter did. They said it was fun and you can download the digital photos for free rather than buy prints in the shop (not just the swing photos). So make sure you keep your QR code card when you enter.
